 Green Thai Curry 500g chicken breasts, sliced 1 onion, finely chopped 200g green beans 1 tbs sunflower oil 1 clove garlic, finely chopped 2 tbs green Thai curry paste 400ml can coconut milk 2 tbs Thai fish sauce 1 tbs honey 2 tbs lemon juice Handful of basil leaves Handful of fresh coriander eaves  Method Heat oil and fry onions until soft. Add Thai curry paste and garlic. Add coconut milk, fish sauce, honey, lemon and simmer for 3 minutes. Add chicken and green beans. Simmer for 8 minutes until chicken is cooked. Serve with jasmine rice and garnish with basil and coriander leaves. Happy cooking, until next week. 